FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* | where qualys_was.vulnerability.detection_score > 0 | SORT qualys_was.vulnerability.detection_score DESC | sort @timestamp DESC

query.esql: FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* | KEEP qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id, qualys_was.vulnerability.type | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id) BY qualys_was.vulnerability.type

FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* | KEEP qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id, qualys_was.vulnerability.type | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id) BY qualys_was.vulnerability.type

embeddableConfig.description:
Counts by Status.  If a detection was found more than once in the time range for the dashboard, the detections are deduplicated for each status. For example, if a detection was found 1 time in the "NEW" state, and 6 times in the "ACTIVE" state, it will be counted once for 
"NEW" and once for "ACTIVE"

query.esql:
FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* 
| KEEP qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id, qualys_was.vulnerability.status,qualys_was.vulnerability.is_ignored | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id) BY qualys_was.vulnerability.status
